  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the best resources to learn typing?",
  "response": "Learning to type efficiently can be a valuable skill, and there are numerous resources available to help you improve your typing speed and accuracy. Here are some of the best resources for learning typing:\n\n### Online Typing Tutorials and Websites\n1. **Typing.com**: Offers free typing lessons, exercises, and games. Suitable for all levels, from beginners to advanced typists.\n2. **Keybr.com**: Focuses on touch typing and presents exercises that adapt to your skill level.\n3. **TypingClub.com**: Provides a comprehensive typing curriculum with engaging lessons, videos, and games.\n4. **Ratatype**: Features typing courses and speed tests to improve your typing efficiency. It also offers certification.\n5. **10FastFingers**: A fun website that allows you to test your typing speed and compete with others in typing races.\n\n### Typing Software\n6. **Mavis Beacon Teaches Typing**: A long-standing typing tutor software that offers customized lesson plans and progress tracking.\n7. **TypingMaster**: A software that provides structured lessons, skill tests, and typing games to enhance your typing skills.\n8. **RapidTyping**: Free typing tutor software designed to improve typing speed and accuracy through various customizable lessons.\n\n### Typing Games\n9. **NitroType**: A competitive typing racing game that makes practicing fun by racing against others online.\n10. **Ztype**: A space-themed typing game that combines typing practice with action gameplay.\n\n### Typing Apps for Mobile Devices\n11. **Typewriter**: Offers typing lessons and games for mobile devices, suitable for learning to type on touchscreens.\n12. **Typing Fingers**: Provides an engaging way to learn touch typing on iOS and Android devices.\n\n### Books and Guides\n13. **\"Learn Touch Typing in a Week\" by Barbara Diamond**: A book offering structured exercises to improve typing skills.\n14. **\"Typing Practice: Searching for Speed and Accuracy\" by James Wyatt**: A practical guide with exercises designed to increase speed and accuracy.\n\n### Community and Forums\n15. **r/typing** (Reddit)**: Participate in discussions, tips, and advice from fellow typing enthusiasts and experts.\n\n### Tips for Improving Typing Skills:\n- **Practice Regularly**: Consistency is key. Dedicate time each day to practice typing.\n- **Use Proper Finger Positioning**: Learn the correct finger placement for touch typing to increase speed and reduce errors.\n- **Focus on Accuracy**: Initially, concentrate on typing accurately without looking at the keyboard. Speed will naturally increase with practice.\n- **Take Breaks**: Typing for long periods can strain your fingers and hands, so remember to take breaks.\n\nCombining these resources and maintaining a regular practice schedule will greatly improve your typing skills over time.",
